data.text:
David Fisher has over 25 years of experience in the music industry, including record deals with Interscope, Geffen Records, and Big Machine Records.

He has worked and recorded with producers, T. Bone Burnett, Roy Thomas Baker, and Nathan Chapman, among other prominent musicians. Following his career as a recording artist, David founded Songs for Film & T.V. in 2010, a music services agency specializing in music creation and curation. David and his team have secured thousands of placements in advertising, film, television and video games for clients such as Fitbit, AT&T, Samsung, 3M, BMW, Comcast, Airbnb, Reebok, MINI, Sheraton, Mobile Strike, Massage Envy, REI, Revlon, Tetris, Blue Moon, Google, Nationwide, NBA 2K, Audi, Gevalia, Under Armour, PlayStation, and Phillips 76/Conoco.
